      {
         "id": "SECTION_nordic",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<h3>The Norse Discovery</h3><p>When comparing the Iberian and Norse perspectives, two essential similarities stand out:<ul><li>Leif Ericsson is considered the first European to discover America (<i>Abya Yala</i>) (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('45d5b35c-5f81-46e5-b666-c4a6e257a28d'); return false;\">Septhon, J., <htdate0>, pp. 15, 16</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('8f31ba39-e450-4654-b4cf-c01e5793eb5f'); return false;\">Septhon, J., <htdate1>, Chapter 5</a>; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('8b15e438-93b6-4ae1-ab5b-7e150abcbf30'); return false;\">Wallace, B., <htdate2></a>), although Bjarni Herjolfsson had been in the region years earlier (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('9c2fe063-9428-4706-b116-ddb07176bdc3'); return false;\">Sanders, Ralph, <htdate3>, pp. 8</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('43ab9622-2e48-48da-926e-688229fc8b11'); return false;\">Jesús Varela Marcos, Real Academia de la História </a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ac201e1f-39de-48df-9627-7df9aed62dd4'); return false;\">Biblioteca Virtual Miguel de Cervantes</a>). This suggests that the choice of “discoverer” was, in part, arbitrary.</li><li>Indigenous peoples were already living on the continent (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('88294169-d7c1-4c98-9e73-a324470cd808'); return false;\">McGhee, Robert, <htdate4></a>). Thus, the “discoverer” did not find the region for the first time but rather encountered land unknown to him and his community.</li></ul></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
