            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><img src=\"images/ElSalvadorMuseo/Bering.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 3</b>: Map showing passage through the Bering Strait. Photo taken at the National Museum of Anthropology, San Salvador (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('b6ffcac4-7379-4a21-ba3c-326e8cb39129'); return false;\">Museo Nacional de Antrolopogía</a>). Photo taken on <htdate0>, during a visit to the museum.</p><p>Since no written records exist from that period, it is impossible to determine with certainty who “discovered” America (Abya Yala). But we do know that they were Homo sapiens, just like us.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2015",
                     "month": "7",
                     "day": "25"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
